Hello support.  I have Agama wallet working in Windows. At least I did until some hours ago! Now I am getting the following message: Connection error!

Content: Also fails. Download starts but crashes out after 15-20 secs. The checksum file here downloads OK. The download also just failed on my old laptop.

Content: I tried the download in Microsfot Edge (I suppose that's a fancy name for internet explorer?) This time I saw the download start, then there was a security scan and it stopped. Clearly security features are blocking it but I have no idea how to fix that. Solutions found in Google search haven't helped much yet.

Author: PTYX#6840
Content: Try chrome

Author: matspb#7829
Content: Thanks. Yes I tried Chrome, Firefox and IE. None worked.... until  in IE I tricked the defender (I think). I paused the download after  every 10% then restarted.  This seemed to stall the security scan. I got through in stages. Installed  new Agama and can now see my coin again. No connection problem. Thanks for suggestions people.
